publicationStmt.p: The WordHoard Shakespeare is a joint project of the Perseus Project at Tufts University, The Northwestern University Library, and Northwestern University Academic Technologies. It is derived from The Globe Shakespeare , the one-volume version of the Cambridge Shakespeare , edited by W. G. Clark, J. Glover, and W. A. Wright (1891-3). The Internet Shakespeare editions of the quartos and folios have been consulted to create a modern text that observes as closely as possible the morphological and prosodic practices of the earliest editions. Spellings, especially of contracted and hyphenated forms, have been standardized across the corpus. The text has been fully lemmatized and morphosyntactically tagged.

div.head: Act 1, Scene 1
div.stage: Dead March.

Enter the Funeral of KING HENRY the Fifth, attended on by the DUKE OF BEDFORD, Regent of France; the DUKE OF GLOUCESTER, protector; the DUKE OF EXETER, the EARL OF WARWICK, the BISHOP OF WINCHESTER, Heralds, c.

div.head: Act 1, Scene 2
div.stage: Sound a flourish.
Enter CHARLES, ALENCON, and REIGNIER, marching with drum and Soldiers.

l.stage: Here alarum; they are beaten back by the English with great loss.
Re-enter the BASTARD of Orleans, with JOAN LA PUCELLE.
Here they fight, and Joan La Pucelle overcomes.

div.head: Act 1, Scene 3
div.stage: London. Before the Tower.
Enter the DUKE OF GLOUCESTER, with his servingmen in blue coats.

l.stage: Gloucester's men rush at the Tower Gates, and Woodvile the Lieutenant speaks within.
Enter to the Protector at the Tower Gates WINCHESTER and his men in tawny coats.
Here Gloucester's men beat out the Cardinal's men, and enter in the hurly-burly the Mayor of London and his Officers.
Exeunt severally, Gloucester and Winchester with their servingmen.

div.head: Act 1, Scene 4
div.stage: Enter, on the walls, a Master Gunner and his Boy.

l.stage: Enter, on the turrets, the LORDS SALISBURY and TALBOT, SIR WILLIAM GLANDSDALE, SIR THOMAS GARGRAVE, and others.
Enter the Boy with a linstock.
Here they shoot. Salisbury and Gargrave fall.
Here an alarum, and it thunders and lightens.
Here Salisbury lifteth himself up and groans.

div.head: Act 1, Scene 5
div.stage: Here an alarum again; and TALBOT pursueth the DAUPHIN, and driveth him:
then enter JOAN LA PUCELLE, driving Englishmen before her,
and exit after them:
then re-enter TALBOT.

l.stage: A short alarum: then enter the town with soldiers.

div.head: Act 1, Scene 6
div.stage: Enter, on the walls, LA PUCELLE, CHARLES, REIGNIER, ALENCON, and Soldiers,

div.head: Act 2, Scene 1
div.stage: Enter a Sergeant of a band, with two Sentinels.

l.stage: Enter TALBOT, BEDFORD, BURGUNDY, and forces, with scaling-ladders, their drums beating a dead march.
Cry: âSt George,â âA Talbot.â The French leap over the walls in their shirts.
Enter, several ways, the BASTARD of Orleans, ALENCON, and REIGNIER, half ready, and half unready.
Alarum. Enter an English Soldier, crying âA Talbot! a Talbot!â
They fly, leaving their clothes behind.

div.head: Act 2, Scene 2
div.stage: Enter TALBOT, BEDFORD, BURGUNDY, a Captain, and others.

div.head: Act 2, Scene 3
div.stage: Enter the COUNTESS and her Porter.

l.stage: Winds his horn. Drums strike up: a peal of ordnance. Enter Soldiers.

div.head: Act 2, Scene 4
div.stage: Enter the EARLS OF SOMERSET, SUFFOLK, and WARWICK; RICHARD PLANTAGENET, VERNON, and another Lawyer.

div.head: Act 2, Scene 5
div.stage: Enter MORTIMER, brought in a chair, and Gaolers.

l.stage: Exeunt Gaolers, bearing out the body of Mortimer.

div.head: Act 3, Scene 1
div.stage: Flourish. Enter KING, EXETER, GLOUCESTER, WARWICK, SOMERSET, and SUFFOLK; the BISHOP OF WINCHESTER, RICHARD PLANTAGENET, and others. GLOUCESTER offers to put up a bill; WINCHESTER snatches it, and tears it.

l.stage: A noise within, âDown with the tawny-coats!â
Enter servingmen, in skirmish, with Bloody pates.
Sennnet. Flourish. Exeunt all but Exeter.

div.head: Act 3, Scene 2
div.stage: Enter LA PUCELLE disguised, with four Soldiers with sacks upon their backs.

l.stage: Enter CHARLES, the BASTARD of Orleans, ALENCON, REIGNIER, and forces.
Enter LA PUCELLE on the top, thrusting out a torch burning.
An alarum. Enter TALBOT in an excursion.
An alarum: excursions. BEDFORD, brought in sick in a chair.
Enter TALBOT and BURGUNDY without: within LA PUCELLE, CHARLES, BASTARD, ALENCON, and REIG-NIER, on the walls.
The English whisper together in council.
Exeunt all but Bedford and Attendants.
An alarum: excursions. Enter SIR JOHN FALSTAFF and a Captain.
Retreat: excursions. LA PUCELLE, ALENCON, and CHARLES fly.
Bedford dies, and is carried in by two in his chair.
An alarum. Re-enter TALBOT, BURGUNDY, and the rest.

div.head: Act 3, Scene 3
div.stage: Enter CHARLES, the BASTARD of Orleans, ALENCON, LA PUCELLE, and forces.

l.stage: Here sound an English march. Enter, and pass over at a distance, TALBOT and his forces.
French march. Enter the DUKE OF BURGUNDY and forces.

div.head: Act 3, Scene 4
div.stage: Enter the KING, GLOUCESTER, BISHOP OF WINCHESTER, YORK, SUFFOLK, SOMERSET, WARWICK, EXETER: VERNON, BASSET, and others. To them with his Soldiers, TALBOT.

l.stage: Sennet. Flourish. Exeunt all but Vernon and Basset.

div.head: Act 4, Scene 1
div.stage: Enter the KING, GLOUCESTER, BISHOP OF WINCHESTER, YORK, SUFFOLK, SOMERSET, WARWICK, TALBOT, EXETER, the Governor of Paris, and others.

l.stage: Flourish. Exeunt all but York, Warwick, Exeter and Vernon.

div.head: Act 4, Scene 2
div.stage: Enter TALBOT, with trump and drum.

l.stage: Trumpet sounds. Enter General and others. aloft.

div.head: Act 4, Scene 3
div.stage: Enter a Messenger that meets YORK. Enter YORK with trumpet and many Soldiers.

div.head: Act 4, Scene 4
div.stage: Enter SOMERSET, with his army; a Captain of TALBOT'S with him.

div.head: Act 4, Scene 5
div.stage: Enter TALBOT and JOHN, his son.

div.head: Act 4, Scene 6
div.stage: Alarum: excursions, wherein TALBOT'S Son is hemmed about, and TALBOT rescues him.

div.head: Act 4, Scene 7
div.stage: Alarum: excursions. Enter old TALBOT led by a Servant.

l.stage: Enter Soldiers, with the body of young TALBOT.
Enter CHARLES, ALENCON, BURGUNDY, BASTARD, LA PUCELLE, and forces.
Enter SIR WILLIAM LUCY, attended; Herald of the French preceding.

div.head: Act 5, Scene 1
div.stage: Sennet. Enter KING, GLOUCESTER, and EXETER.

l.stage: Enter WINCHESTER in Cardinal's habit, a Legate and two Ambassadors.
Exeunt all but Winchester and Legate.

div.head: Act 5, Scene 2
div.stage: Enter CHARLES, BURGUNDY, ALENCON, BASTARD, REIGNIER, LA PUCELLE and forces.

div.head: Act 5, Scene 3
div.stage: Alarum. Excursions. Enter LA PUCELLE.

l.stage: Excursions. Re-enter LA PUCELLE fighting hand to hand with YORK: LA PUCELLE is taken. The French fly.
Alarum. Enter SUFFOLK, with MARGARET in his hand.
A parley sounded. Enter REIGNIER on the walls.

div.head: Act 5, Scene 4
div.stage: Enter YORK, WARWICK, and others.

l.stage: Enter LA PUCELLE, guarded, and a Shepherd.
Enter CARDINAL BEAUFORT, Bishop of Winchester, attended.
Enter CHARLES, ALENCON, BASTARD, REIGNIER, and others.

div.head: Act 5, Scene 5
div.stage: Enter SUFFOLK in conference with the KING, GLOUCESTER and EXETER.
